==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bland
<hw>Bland</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>blandus</ets>, of unknown origin.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Mild; soft; gentle; smooth and soothing in manner;
suave; <as>as, a bland temper; <ex>bland</ex> persuasion; a
<ex>bland</ex> sycophant</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Exhilarating vapor
<xex>bland</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having soft and soothing qualities; not drastic or
irritating; not stimulating; <as>as, a <ex>bland</ex> oil; a
<ex>bland</ex> diet</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blandation</ent>⟦br⟧
